			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">How this song works...<a name="3545"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 25 03 12:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When you get buffed or DoTed or anything else, you get &quot;counters&quot; added to your character...
<br />

<br />
For example, suppose you get the Spreading Crud from the Plargs in Paludal Caverns. That disease adds a certain number of disease counters to your character. That's why a level 20ish cleric takes 3 casts to get it off, and why a higher level cleric can take it off with 1 cast. The lower level spell takes off X counters (2 or something), and the higher spell takes off more, (36 is one spell I think).
<br />

<br />
There are different types of Counters. The ones I know of are:
<br />
Magic
<br />
Disease
<br />
Poison
<br />
Curse
<br />

<br />
This song removes 9 magic counters. Then it does it again (in the same pulse) as far as I know...
<br />

<br />
The reason they did it in two effects instead of 18 counters in one, is probably because 18 counters in 1 would remove a maximum of 1 effect, whereas doing 9 twice removes a maximum of 2 effects, if each has 9 magic counters or less...
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is mostly assumption and observation, if you disagree feel free to correct me....</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
